** Inner Shrine Subordinate Shrine: Ebisu Shrine – deity: {{ill|Kotoamatsukami|ja|事代主命}}.

* Outer Shrine – Main deity: {{ill|Toyouke-Ōmikami|ja|豊受大御神}}. Additional deities: {{ill|Ninigi-no-Mikoto|ja|天津彦彦火瓊々芸命}}, {{ill|Ame-no-Koyane|ja|天児屋命}}, {{ill|Futodama|ja|天太玉命}}, {{ill|Takeminakata|ja|建御名方神}}, {{ill|Yasakatome|ja|八坂刀自命}}.
** Outer Shrine Auxiliary Shrine: Taga Shrine – Deities: {{ill|Toyouke-hime|lt=Toyouke-Ōmikami (Aramitama)|ja|豊受大御神荒魂}}, {{ill|Iwanaga-hime|ja|伊吹戸主神}}.

Additionally, the precincts feature Taga Shrine and Takamine Inari Shrine, along with Iwato Shrine, located on the mountainside of Mount Kōno.

== Annual Events ==
Initially, Yamaguchi Daijingū performed Shikinen-sengu every 20 years, mirroring Ise Grand Shrine. Although interrupted by wars and financial constraints, the practice resumed intermittently in the modern era. Major reconstructions occurred in 1880 and 1902. The most recent Shikinen-sengu was held in 2000.

== Access ==
* 5 minutes by bus from {{ill|Yamaguchi Station (Yamaguchi)|ja|山口駅}} to Kenchō-mae Bus Stop, then a 5-minute walk.
* Approximately 25 minutes on foot from Yamaguchi Station.

